<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,500,1130,1157]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
Key to subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer &amp; Meyer" authorityYear="1837" box="[383,500,1130,1157]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Rhamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pallasii">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[383,500,1130,1157]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">R. pallasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="134" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1199,1681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="134">1. branches without densely spines; leaves of specimen in each node clearly inequal (long leaves 2 or more times longer than short leaves in each node), narrow, homomorphic, and linear or oblong or rarely narrow lanceolate, more than 5 times longer than wide, lateral nerves mostly in 2–4 pairs.......................................................................................................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1199,1681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="134">- branches with densely spines; leaves of specimen in each node almost unequal, large, polymomorphic (spathulate, elliptic, ovoid, rhomboid, lanceolate), up to 5 times longer than width; lateral nerves mostly in 4–6 pairs..............................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1199,1681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
2. Rocky to pasture habitat; leaves green, monomorphic and mainly oblong; main vein white or green; petioles green; obtuse at apex; leaves up to 8 time longer than wide; anthers oblong, lateral nerves mostly 3–4 pairs; N, C &amp; W 
<collectingCountry box="[1413,1452,1372,1393]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">Iran</collectingCountry>
................................................................................................................................................. 3b. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer &amp; Meyer" authorityYear="1837" box="[1130,1229,1400,1422]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Rhamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pallasii">
<emphasis box="[1130,1145,1401,1422]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1157,1229,1400,1421]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">pallasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. subsp 
<emphasis box="[1301,1450,1400,1421]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">mazandaranica</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1199,1681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
- Rocky and cliff habitat; leaves greenish yellow, monomorphic and linear; main vein greenish yellow; petioles cream; acute at apex; leaves more than 8 time longer than wide; anthers elliptic, lateral nerves mostly 2–3 pairs; W &amp; C (rarely) N 
<collectingCountry box="[1257,1296,1458,1479]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">Iran</collectingCountry>
......................... ............................................................................................................................................................... 3a. 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. pallasii" box="[1207,1451,1487,1509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Rhamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pallasii" subSpecies="pallasii">
<emphasis box="[1207,1306,1487,1508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">R. pallasii</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1379,1451,1487,1508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">pallasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1199,1681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
3. Plants spreading, up to 
<quantity box="[443,516,1515,1537]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" unit="cm" value="150.0">150 cm</quantity>
high; stems mostly dark grey; branches with many intricate spines; mainly with open (obtuse) angles; leaves polymorphic, with regular deep marginal teeth; lateral nerves conspicuous, leaves length up to 2.5 times longer than wide; obtuse or acute at apex; flower about 
<quantity box="[631,686,1573,1595]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
high; N &amp; EN 
<collectingCountry box="[833,872,1574,1595]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">Iran</collectingCountry>
..............................................3c. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer &amp; Meyer" authorityYear="1837" box="[1187,1285,1573,1595]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Rhamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pallasii">
<emphasis box="[1187,1285,1573,1595]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">R. pallasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1297,1451,1573,1595]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Rhamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pallasii" subSpecies="sintenisii">
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1364,1451,1574,1595]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">sintenisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1199,1681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
- Plants erect, up to 
<quantity box="[385,455,1602,1623]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" unit="cm" value="300.0">300 cm</quantity>
high; stems mostly brownish yellow; branches with a few spines; not intricate, mainly with close (sharp) angles; leaves dimorphic, with irreregular superficial marginal teeth; lateral nerves inconspicuous, rarely with entire leaves; leaves length 2.5 time longer than width; obtuse at apex; flowers 
<quantity box="[771,850,1659,1681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 mm</quantity>
high; W &amp; C 
<collectingCountry box="[986,1025,1660,1681]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">Iran</collectingCountry>
............ 3d. 
